sources.description:
In the Shadows of London, a Young Boy's Courage Shines -  A Journey of Survival and Hope in the Heart of London!
This 1933 adaptation of "Oliver Twist" brings to life the adventures of a brave orphan struggling to survive in a ruthless city. Along his journey, Oliver encounters danger and deception but ultimately finds love and redemption.

Original title: Oliver Twist (1933)

Black & White version: https://youtu.be/ImmD2MrkIzw


Director: William J. Cowen
Writers: Charles Dickens (novel), Elizabeth Meehan (script)
Genres: Colorized, Classics, Drama, Mystery, Family, Literary
